The '''1987 Football League Second Division play-off Final''' was contested by [[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]] and [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]].

After two legs at [[Elland Road]] and [[Selhurst Park]] (Charlton's home ground at the time) the two teams were tied 1-1 on aggregate, each team having won their home tie 1-0 meaning the away goal rule couldn't separate the sides.  A one-off decider was arranged at [[St Andrews (stadium)|St. Andrews]].

After full time the score was 0-0 meaning extra time was needed.  [[John Sheridan (footballer)|John Sheridan]] scored first for Leeds in the 99th minute, however [[Peter Shirtliff]] scored twice in the 113th and 117th minute to ensure Charlton kept their top flight status.

